%description
A set of functions for two-dimensional sociometric status determination
with rating scales. For each person assessed, SSrat computes probability
distributions of the total scores for `Sympathy' (S), `Antipathy' (A),
social `Preference' (P) and social `Impact' (I), and applies a set of
criteria for sociometric status categorization.

